start-meta EXPERIMENT
 delay-check-ENTRY ["FGM"]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT
end-meta EXPERIMENT
start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
end-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION

 delay-check-ENTRY ["identical spacecraft that will flight in a tetrahedral configuration. The separation distances "]

 delay-check-ENTRY ["and its environment in three dimensions. To achieve this, Cluster is constituted of four "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["identical spacecraft that will flight in a tetrahedral configuration. The separation distances "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["between the spacecraft will be varied between ~40 km and 10 000 km, according to the "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["key scientific regions."]

start-meta EXPERIMENT
 delay-check-ENTRY ["FGM"]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT
end-meta EXPERIMENT
start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
end-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
end-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]

 delay-check-ENTRY ["The aim of the Cluster mission is to study small-scale structures of the magnetosphere "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["and its environment in three dimensions. To achieve this, Cluster is constituted of four "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["identical spacecraft that will flight in a tetrahedral configuration. The separation distances "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["between the spacecraft will be varied between ~40 km and 10 000 km, according to the "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["key scientific regions."]

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
end-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
end-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION

start-meta EXPERIMENT
 delay-check-ENTRY ["FGM"]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
end-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION

 delay-check-ENTRY ["and its environment in three dimensions. To achieve this, Cluster is constituted of four "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["identical spacecraft that will flight in a tetrahedral configuration. The separation distances "]

start-meta EXPERIMENT

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
end-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
end-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION

 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]

 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
end-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION

 delay-check-ENTRY ["FGM"]

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
end-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]

 delay-check-ENTRY ["The aim of the Cluster mission is to study small-scale structures of the magnetosphere "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["and its environment in three dimensions. To achieve this, Cluster is constituted of four "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["identical spacecraft that will flight in a tetrahedral configuration. The separation distances "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["between the spacecraft will be varied between ~40 km and 10 000 km, according to the "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["key scientific regions."]

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
end-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION

 delay-check-ENTRY ["FGM"]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
end-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]

 delay-check-ENTRY ["The aim of the Cluster mission is to study small-scale structures of the magnetosphere "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["and its environment in three dimensions. To achieve this, Cluster is constituted of four "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["identical spacecraft that will flight in a tetrahedral configuration. The separation distances "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["between the spacecraft will be varied between ~40 km and 10 000 km, according to the "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["key scientific regions."]

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
end-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION

start-meta EXPERIMENT
 delay-check-ENTRY ["FGM"]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT
end-meta EXPERIMENT
start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
end-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]

 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
end-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
end-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]

start-meta EXPERIMENT

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
end-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
end-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION

start-meta EXPERIMENT

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
end-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION

 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]

 delay-check-ENTRY ["identical spacecraft that will flight in a tetrahedral configuration. The separation distances "]

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
end-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION

start-meta MISSION_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The aim of the Cluster mission is to study small-scale structures of the magnetosphere "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["and its environment in three dimensions. To achieve this, Cluster is constituted of four "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["identical spacecraft that will flight in a tetrahedral configuration. The separation distances "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["between the spacecraft will be varied between ~40 km and 10 000 km, according to the "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["key scientific regions."]

start-meta EXPERIMENT
 delay-check-ENTRY ["FGM"]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT
end-meta EXPERIMENT
start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
end-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION

 delay-check-ENTRY ["Chris Carr>PI>c.m.carr@imperial.ac.uk"]

 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]

 delay-check-ENTRY ["and its environment in three dimensions. To achieve this, Cluster is constituted of four "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["identical spacecraft that will flight in a tetrahedral configuration. The separation distances "]

start-meta EXPERIMENT
 delay-check-ENTRY ["FGM"]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT
end-meta EXPERIMENT
start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
end-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION

start-meta EXPERIMENT
 delay-check-ENTRY ["FGM"]

end-meta EXPERIMENT
start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
end-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION

 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION

 delay-check-ENTRY ["The aim of the Cluster mission is to study small-scale structures of the magnetosphere "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["and its environment in three dimensions. To achieve this, Cluster is constituted of four "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["identical spacecraft that will flight in a tetrahedral configuration. The separation distances "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["between the spacecraft will be varied between ~40 km and 10 000 km, according to the "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["key scientific regions."]

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
end-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]

start-meta EXPERIMENT
 delay-check-ENTRY ["FGM"]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT
end-meta EXPERIMENT
start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
end-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION

start-meta EXPERIMENT
 delay-check-ENTRY ["FGM"]

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
end-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
end-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION

 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]

 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]

 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]

 delay-check-ENTRY ["identical spacecraft that will flight in a tetrahedral configuration. The separation distances "]

start-meta EXPERIMENT

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
end-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
end-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]

 delay-check-ENTRY ["The aim of the Cluster mission is to study small-scale structures of the magnetosphere "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["and its environment in three dimensions. To achieve this, Cluster is constituted of four "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["identical spacecraft that will flight in a tetrahedral configuration. The separation distances "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["between the spacecraft will be varied between ~40 km and 10 000 km, according to the "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["key scientific regions."]

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
end-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION

 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]
 ok-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION

 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]

 delay-check-ENTRY ["and its environment in three dimensions. To achieve this, Cluster is constituted of four "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["identical spacecraft that will flight in a tetrahedral configuration. The separation distances "]

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]

 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]

start-meta EXPERIMENT_DESCRIPTION
 delay-check-ENTRY ["Each Cluster spacecraft carries an identical FGM instrument"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(Fluxgate Magnetometer) to measure the DC magnetic field"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["vector. Each instrument, in turn, consists of two triaxial"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["fluxgate magnetometers and an onboard data processing unit."]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["The instrument samples the magnetic field at a cadence of 22 Hz"]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(67 Hz in Burst mode). In order to minimise the magnetic "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["background of the spacecraft, one of the magnetometer sensors"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" (the outboard, or OB sensor) is located at the end of one"]
 delay-check-ENTRY [" of the two 5 m radial booms of the spacecraft, the other "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["(the inboard, or IB sensor) at 1.5 m inboard from the end "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["of the boom. Since the start of the scientific operations "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["on February 1, 2001, only the outboard sensor on each "]
 delay-check-ENTRY ["satellite has been used."]
